.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(originally as 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED78381CFE30F8C0FD13F8E9" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="1972" box="[501,726,1806,1832]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Demoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusiforma">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFE30F8C0FD13F8E9" box="[501,726,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">Demoixys fusiforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), by original designation
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED78381CFF78F89CFF36F813" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED78381CFF78F89CFF36F813" blockId="553.[136,778,1125,2070]" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFF78F89CFEFBF8AD" bold="true" box="[189,318,1874,1900]" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">Etymology</emphasis>
. From “ 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFE7EF89CFE0CF8AA" box="[443,457,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">a</emphasis>
” (Greek prefix meaning “not”) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED78381CFE1EF8BAFD8CF84C" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[475,585,1908,1933]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Demoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFE1EF8BAFD8CF84C" box="[475,585,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">Demoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to the differences between the new genus and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED78381CFDF9F858FD6FF86E" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[572,682,1942,1967]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Demoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFDF9F858FD6FF86E" box="[572,682,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">Demoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED78381CFF78F814FB34FE74" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED78381CFF78F814FB34FE74" blockId="553.[136,778,1125,2070]" lastBlockId="553.[810,1452,173,437]" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFF78F814FEEFF835" bold="true" box="[189,298,2010,2036]" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED78381CFE87F814FE22F835" author="Ooishi, S." box="[322,487,2010,2036]" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" pagination="303 - 325" part="19" refId="ref330320" refString="Ooishi, S. (1972) Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 19 (5), 303 - 325. https: // doi. org / 10.5134 / 175727" title="Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan" type="journal article" year="1972">Ooishi (1972)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED78381CFDB6F814FCCCF835" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="1972" box="[627,777,2010,2036]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Demoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusiforma">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFDB6F814FCCCF835" box="[627,777,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">D. fusiforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on material found living in association with the ascidian 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED78381CFC01FF63FAD3FF06" authority="(Oka, 1927)" baseAuthorityName="Oka" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[964,1302,173,199]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Holozoidae" genus="Distaplia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFC01FF63FBBFFF06" box="[964,1146,173,199]" italics="true" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">Distaplia dubia</emphasis>
(Oka, 1927)
</taxonomicName>
in Japanese waters. This copepod differs fundamentally from known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED78381CFC61FF3CFBD7FECA" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[932,1042,242,267]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Demoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFC61FF3CFBD7FECA" box="[932,1042,242,267]" italics="true" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">Demoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so the new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED78381CFB3DFF3FFAB4FECA" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1272,1393,241,267]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Ademoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFB3DFF3FFAB4FECA" box="[1272,1393,241,267]" italics="true" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">Ademoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED78381CFABFFF3FFC9EFEEC" bold="true" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED78381CFABFFF3FFC9EFEEC" pageId="553" pageNumber="554" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, is established to accommodate it as 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED78381CFADDFEDDFA8DFEEC" box="[1304,1352,275,301]" pageId="553" pageNumber="554">type</typeStatus>
species. The significant features defining the new genus are the transformation of the coxal gnathobase of the mandible into a powerful hook, the fusiform body, and the distinct butunarmed rami of the swimming legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
